video.title: Dawson's Creek
video.synopsis: Close-knit teens Dawson, Joey, Pacey and Jen explore the highs and lows of high school and beyond, fueled by dreams, desires and ever-present drama.

episodes.synopsis: A pair of childhood friends must cope with their emerging sexuality.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Dawson worries about his first kiss with Jen, especially when she attends a school dance with someone else.
episodes.title: Dance

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson is forced to work on a rival's film, he plots to record his first kiss with Jen. Meanwhile, Joey misleads a wealthy suitor.
episodes.title: Kiss

episodes.synopsis: After videotaping Tamara's sexual encounter with an unknown partner and learning of his mom's infidelity, Dawson discovers the truth about Jen's past.
episodes.title: Discovery

episodes.synopsis: Preparations for a big hurricane expose the truth about Mrs. Leery's affair.
episodes.title: Hurricane

episodes.synopsis: As word of Pacey's affair with Tamara gets out, Bessie must seek help from Grams to deliver her baby.
episodes.title: Baby

episodes.synopsis: The conflicts brewing among Dawson and his friends erupt during their detention.
episodes.title: Detention

episodes.synopsis: Jen's former boyfriend arrives unexpectedly, and Dawson's parents struggle with their relationship.
episodes.title: Boyfriend

episodes.synopsis: Jen's ex-boyfriend takes Dawson and Pacey to a nightclub. Meanwhile, Joey strikes back after learning that she's the subject of nasty rumors.
episodes.title: Roadtrip

episodes.synopsis: Dawson arranges a double date with Jen and her new boyfriend, and an extra-credit assignment brings Pacey and Joey together.
episodes.title: Double Date

episodes.synopsis: While Dawson is preparing to celebrate Friday the 13th, a serial killer is rumored to be headed to Capeside.
episodes.title: The Scare

episodes.synopsis: Joey and Pacey enter a beauty pageant.
episodes.title: Beauty Contest

episodes.synopsis: An offer to study abroad forces Joey and Dawson to reconsider their feelings for each other, and Jen's grandfather suddenly awakens from his coma.
episodes.title: Decisions

episodes.synopsis: Dawson and Joey embark on a romance as Jen tries to cope with the loss of her grandfather.
episodes.title: The Kiss

episodes.synopsis: Dawson's preoccupation with Joey causes him to forget Pacey's 16th birthday.
episodes.title: Crossroads

episodes.synopsis: A class assignment gives Jen a chance to win back Dawson, while Pacey learns the truth about Andie's wealth.
episodes.title: Alternative Lifestyles

episodes.synopsis: Tamara's return dredges up unresolved feelings in Pacey, and Joey struggles for independence from Dawson.
episodes.title: Tamara's Return

episodes.synopsis: Dawson confronts his parents about their marriage as Pacey stumbles onto an unsettling truth about Andie.
episodes.title: Full Moon Rising

episodes.synopsis: A homecoming dance brings Pacey and Andie together while driving Dawson and Joey apart.
episodes.title: The Dance

episodes.synopsis: An all-night study session creates friction and produces some surprises for Dawson and his friends.
episodes.title: The All-Nighter

episodes.synopsis: As a film festival prize fails to reunite Dawson and Joey, Andie sets out to help Pacey get his life on track.
episodes.title: The Reluctant Hero

episodes.synopsis: In their bid for student council, Andie and Joey face a nasty smear campaign. Meanwhile, Jen tries to get Dawson to embrace being a teenager.
episodes.title: The Election

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson's new film exposes his uncertainty about his relationship with Joey, Pacey and Andie explore the idea of having sex.
episodes.title: High Risk Behavior

episodes.synopsis: When an unsigned letter reveals that a couple has been having sex, Abby sets out to expose the guilty pair.
episodes.title: Sex, She Wrote

episodes.synopsis: As a fishing tournament provides a chance for father-son bonding, Gail's report about teenage girls exposes the friction between Jen and Joey.
episodes.title: Uncharted Waters

episodes.synopsis: Dawson's new film mirrors his failed romance with Joey, and the truth about Andie's medication stuns Pacey.
episodes.title: His Leading Lady

episodes.synopsis: When a harsh teacher forces Jack to read a poem that leads everyone to suspect he's gay, Pacey's principled defense threatens to get him suspended.
episodes.title: To Be or Not to Be... (Part 1)

episodes.synopsis: As rumors about Jack's sexuality continue unabated, Pacey sets out to stop a teacher's relentless harassment.
episodes.title: ... That Is the Question (Part 2)

episodes.synopsis: Dawson's surprise 16th birthday party goes awry when he and Andie show up drunk.
episodes.title: Be Careful What You Wish For

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson solicits a teacher's opinion of his film, Joey pursues a date with someone who's interested in Jack.
episodes.title: Psychic Friends

episodes.synopsis: A Capeside wedding forces Joey to face her family's reputation.
episodes.title: A Perfect Wedding

episodes.synopsis: Abby's drowning causes Jen to lose faith in everything and forces Joey to confront her mother's death.
episodes.title: Abby Morgan, Rest in Peace

episodes.synopsis: Dawson and Joey's romantic dinner is spoiled by his parents' presence, and Pacey suspects that Andie is seeing someone else.
episodes.title: Reunited

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson looks for a subject for his film class final, Andie and Jack's father insists on moving them away from Capeside.
episodes.title: Ch... Ch... Ch... Changes

episodes.synopsis: While Dawson wrestles with Mr. Potter's drug dealing, Pacey squares off with his father.
episodes.title: Parental Discretion Advised

episodes.synopsis: After a summer away, Dawson returns to face a decision about Joey, and Jen uses cheerleading tryouts to teach someone a lesson.
episodes.title: Like a Virgin

episodes.synopsis: Dawson's first sexual encounter with Eve produces a big surprise. Meanwhile, Pacey discovers that Andie had an affair.
episodes.title: Homecoming

episodes.synopsis: Dawson faces an ethical dilemma when Eve gives him an advance copy of a college entrance exam.
episodes.title: None of the Above

episodes.synopsis: Dawson makes a documentary about Jack, Capeside's gay football star.
episodes.title: Home Movies

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson tries to uncover the mystery surrounding Eve, Joey's boss turns his attention to Andie.
episodes.title: Indian Summer

episodes.synopsis: Jen hosts a tea for Capeside's former homecoming queens, and Andie tries to win back Pacey.
episodes.title: Secrets and Lies

episodes.synopsis: Dawson enlists his friends to make a documentary about a local witch legend.
episodes.title: Escape from Witch Island

episodes.synopsis: Jen's mother makes an unexpected appearance at Thanksgiving.
episodes.title: Guess Who's Coming to Dinner?

episodes.synopsis: Dawson suspects Pacey and Joey of having an affair. Meanwhile, Andie encourages Jack to arrange a blind date with another gay teen.
episodes.title: Four to Tango

episodes.synopsis: In Boston -- where Dawson has entered a film festival -- Andie and Joey make a college campus visit while Jack explores the city's gay scene.
episodes.title: First Encounters of the Close Kind

episodes.synopsis: Jack looks for his first gay experience, and Dawson finds a rival sympathetic to his parents' divorce.
episodes.title: Barefoot at Capefest

episodes.synopsis: Everyone rallies to make a good impression after Pacey arranges for an influential travel writer to visit the Potter sisters' new inn.
episodes.title: A Weekend in the Country

episodes.synopsis: Pacey's stage fright threatens to ruin the school play's opening night, and Joey agrees to date a college student.
episodes.title: Northern Lights

episodes.synopsis: Pacey persuades Dawson and their friends to attend a wild Valentine's Day party.
episodes.title: Valentine's Day Massacre

episodes.synopsis: Pacey seeks revenge after a vandal's attack on Joey's school mural, and Andie's guilt deepens after learning the results of her college entrance exam.
episodes.title: Crime and Punishment

episodes.synopsis: Joey rallies her friends and family in support of Capeside High's embattled principal.
episodes.title: To Green, With Love

episodes.synopsis: Joey learns that there's someone else in A.J.'s life, and Dawson tries to help his mother open the new restaurant.
episodes.title: Cinderella Story

episodes.synopsis: While Pacey sets out to tell Dawson about his feelings for Joey, she tries to avoid another kiss.
episodes.title: Neverland

episodes.synopsis: A spring break trip to see Dawson's aunt brings Pacey and Joey closer. Meanwhile, Jen becomes jealous when another woman pursues Henry.
episodes.title: Stolen Kisses

episodes.synopsis: Joey and Pacey break their news to Dawson.
episodes.title: The Longest Day

episodes.synopsis: Dawson and Pacey use a regatta to wage a war for Joey's affections.
episodes.title: Show Me Love

episodes.synopsis: Dawson organizes an alternative junior prom.
episodes.title: The Anti-Prom

episodes.synopsis: Dawson realizes he's standing in the way of Joey's happiness, and Grams insists that Jen and Jack mend their damaged love lives before it's too late.
episodes.title: True Love

episodes.synopsis: Uncertainty is in the air as Pacey and Joey return to Capeside after their summer-long voyage.
episodes.title: Coming Home

episodes.synopsis: As the new school year finds Pacey on the verge of flunking out, Joey goes to work at the yacht club.
episodes.title: Failing Down

episodes.synopsis: Dawson and Joey are forced to try to save the lives of Pacey and Jen when they're threatened by a hurricane.
episodes.title: The Two Gentlemen of Capeside

episodes.synopsis: As the college application process intensifies, Gretchen lands a job as bartender at Gail's restaurant.
episodes.title: Future Tense

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson discovers that his mother is pregnant, Joey struggles with deciding when to become intimate with Pacey.
episodes.title: A Family Way

episodes.synopsis: Andie celebrates her admission to Harvard by attending a rave, which ends up endangering her life.
episodes.title: Great Xpectations

episodes.synopsis: An opportunity for time off before starting college prompts Andie to try to bring everyone together before she leaves.
episodes.title: You Had Me at Goodbye

episodes.synopsis: Dawson, Pacey and Jack become the suspects in a senior class prank.
episodes.title: The Unusual Suspects

episodes.synopsis: Dawson seeks Mr. Brooks' advice about becoming a director, and Joey takes Pacey along to a dinner at an exclusive college.
episodes.title: Kiss Kiss Bang Bang

episodes.synopsis: As Mr. Brooks' revelations about his past inspire Dawson, Pacey is encouraged to push his relationship with Joey.
episodes.title: Self-Reliance

episodes.synopsis: Pacey tries to disrupt Dawson's efforts to woo Gretchen, and Drue's mischief ends with him and Joey locked inside a storage closet.
episodes.title: The Tao of Dawson

episodes.synopsis: Joey's surprise birthday party for Pacey amplifies long-simmering emotional tensions in the Witter family.
episodes.title: The Te of Pacey

episodes.synopsis: Dawson is uncomfortable about meeting Gretchen's friends, and Joey and Pacey are enlisted to help Drue get through an important date.
episodes.title: Hopeless

episodes.synopsis: With his friends away on a senior class ski trip, Dawson discovers that he's been given the power over Mr. Brooks' life.
episodes.title: A Winter's Tale

episodes.synopsis: As Pacey and Joey analyze their first sexual experience, Mr. Brooks' death brings Dawson and Gretchen's relationship into focus.
episodes.title: Four Stories

episodes.synopsis: Pacey and Joey's efforts to spend a night together create an opportunity for Dawson and Gretchen, and Jen enlists Jack to help spy on her therapist.
episodes.title: Mind Games

episodes.synopsis: The excitement over Joey's college admission dims when she learns the price of tuition.
episodes.title: Admissions

episodes.synopsis: Senior Ditch Day sends Dawson and Gretchen on a road trip to Maine. Meanwhile, Jen heads to New York City for a showdown with her father.
episodes.title: Eastern Standard Time

episodes.synopsis: As Gail awaits the birth of her overdue baby, Joey worries that she may be pregnant.
episodes.title: Late

episodes.synopsis: While sparking a pair of possible romances, Capeside's senior prom threatens the future of two other budding relationships.
episodes.title: Promicide

episodes.synopsis: Gretchen's return to college forces Dawson to make an important decision, and Jen balks when Grams wants to sell the house to pay for her tuition.
episodes.title: Separation Anxiety

episodes.synopsis: Graduation for the Class of 2001 brings friends and family back together but will soon drive them apart.
episodes.title: The Graduate

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson prepares to leave for college, he and Joey reunite to say goodbye.
episodes.title: Coda

episodes.synopsis: Though they've all left Capeside for school and other pursuits, things between Joey, Dawson, Jen, Jack and Pacey remain unsettled.
episodes.title: The Bostonians

episodes.synopsis: Joey's grim phone message undercuts Dawson's trip to Boston, and Jen decides to give romance a chance.
episodes.title: The Lost Weekend

episodes.synopsis: Dawson's decision to drop out of film school is frowned upon by his father, and Joey learns about Pacey's presence in Boston.
episodes.title: Capeside Revisited

episodes.synopsis: Dawson's friends look for ways to help ease the pain as he takes on the responsibility of holding the family together after his father's death.
episodes.title: The Long Goodbye

episodes.synopsis: As Joey eagerly prepares for a visit from Dawson, Jack is forced to choose between his fraternity brothers and Tobey.
episodes.title: Use Your Disillusion

episodes.synopsis: While in Boston to see a psychiatrist about his anxiety attacks, Dawson learns that his friends' lives are also in turmoil.
episodes.title: High Anxiety

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson begins therapy, Joey looks for the self-confidence to voice her opinions. Meanwhile, Pacey discovers the truth about Danny's affair.
episodes.title: Text, Lies and Videotape

episodes.synopsis: As Joey and Audrey join Jack and his friends at a fraternity formal, Dawson invites Jen to join him for a weekend in New Hampshire.
episodes.title: Hotel New Hampshire

episodes.synopsis: Jen solicits four scary stories during her Halloween night stint as a substitute DJ at the campus radio station.
episodes.title: Four Scary Stories

episodes.synopsis: Dawson and Jen return home to an unexpected dinner party where their new relationship is suddenly unveiled.
episodes.title: Appetite for Destruction

episodes.synopsis: Jen tries to persuade Dawson to move to Boston, while Joey, Pacey and Audrey get together for a night to celebrate their respective achievements.
episodes.title: Something Wild

episodes.synopsis: As Pacey is forced to choose between a new passion and an old one, Dawson and Jen try to find balance in their new relationship.
episodes.title: Sleeping Arrangements

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson starts film school, Jen's new happiness threatens her radio show. Meanwhile, Joey ends up with two dinner dates and a tough choice to make.
episodes.title: Something Wilder

episodes.synopsis: While Dawson struggles to direct a classmate's script, Joey faces her feelings about Prof. Wilder.
episodes.title: Guerilla Filmmaking

episodes.synopsis: Joey helps a mugger who robbed her just before being hit by a car.
episodes.title: Downtown Crossing

episodes.synopsis: Jen and Pacey get some unexpected advice about romance from a pair of touring musicians.
episodes.title: In a Lonely Place

episodes.synopsis: As Audrey and Pacey join Joey on a road trip to perform with Charlie's band, Dawson's return to Capeside reveals new information about his mom's life.
episodes.title: Highway to Hell

episodes.synopsis: Dawson inadvertently insults an influential critic just before she's about to review his new film.
episodes.title: Cigarette Burns

episodes.synopsis: While a spring break trip forces Pacey and Audrey to admit their true feelings for each other, Joey must decide how to handle a persistent Charlie.
episodes.title: 100 Light Years from Home

episodes.synopsis: As a tour for Charlie's band leaves Joey with a big decision, Pacey and Audrey find that the restaurant's new ownership means big changes for them.
episodes.title: Separate Ways (Worlds Apart)

episodes.synopsis: While Pacey tries to resist the temptations offered by Alex, a study break leads Dawson into bed with a film critic.
episodes.title: After Hours

episodes.synopsis: The end of the school year sees Dawson and his friends struggling to go their separate ways.
episodes.title: The Abby

episodes.synopsis: At the airport, everyone's best-laid summer vacation plans are thrown into disarray.
episodes.title: Swan Song

episodes.synopsis: An end-of-summer reunion in Boston reignites Dawson and Joey's long-simmering romance.
episodes.title: The Kids Are Alright

episodes.synopsis: The news of Dawson's summer romance in Los Angeles upends his efforts to woo Joey.
episodes.title: The Song Remains the Same

episodes.synopsis: Joey accidentally sends a heartfelt e-mail meant for Dawson to the entire Worthington campus.
episodes.title: The Importance of Not Being Too Earnest

episodes.synopsis: As the arrival of the film's star creates problems for Dawson, Audrey catches Pacey out on the town when he's supposed to be studying.
episodes.title: Instant Karma!

episodes.synopsis: While Dawson goes all out to keep Natasha in the picture, Audrey is offered a chance to sing with Emma's band.
episodes.title: The Imposters

episodes.synopsis: A worried Dawson suspects a ghost is haunting the set and that Todd and Natasha are rekindling their affair.
episodes.title: Living Dead Girl

episodes.synopsis: Audrey's drinking forces Joey to see how her roommate's life is spinning out of control.
episodes.title: Ego Tripping at the Gates of Hell

episodes.synopsis: Jen's efforts to reunite Pacey and his girlfriend at a No Doubt concert backfire when the truth about C.J. and Audrey comes out.
episodes.title: Spiderwebs

episodes.synopsis: Spending the night at Eddie's puts Joey at risk of losing her scholarship, and Emma agrees to be Pacey's date for an office party.
episodes.title: Everything Put Together Falls Apart

episodes.synopsis: An out-of-control Audrey brings Christmas dinner at the Leery house crashing down -- literally.
episodes.title: Merry Mayhem

episodes.synopsis: As completion of the film creates an unanticipated opportunity for Dawson, Joey comes face to face with Prof. Hetson's unruly teenage daughter.
episodes.title: Day Out of Days

episodes.synopsis: While Audrey gets a second chance and Pacey is offered an unexpected promotion at work, Joey is reunited with Eddie.
episodes.title: All the Right Moves

episodes.synopsis: Joey recruits Eddie for a cross-country trek to get Audrey into rehab, and Dawson finds that directing in Hollywood is harder than he imagined.
episodes.title: Rock Bottom

episodes.synopsis: Pacey and Jack throw a party replete with surprises, and a visit to see Audrey in rehab brings Dawson face to face with a moviemaking legend.
episodes.title: Clean and Sober

episodes.synopsis: In his rush to make a hastily arranged date with a beautiful stranger, Pacey ends up locked inside a store with Joey overnight.
episodes.title: Castaways

episodes.synopsis: As Dawson returns to Capeside High to discuss his career, Pacey is drawn back home by his father's heart attack.
episodes.title: That Was Then

episodes.synopsis: As Joey is drafted to fill in as Pacey's assistant, Dawson receives a tempting offer to make a film that he doesn't believe in.
episodes.title: Sex and Violence

episodes.synopsis: While Eddie's unexpected return throws Joey for a loop, Dawson comes home to complete his script.
episodes.title: Love Bites

episodes.synopsis: A benefit session of "Loveline" exposes the problems brewing between Joey and Eddie, Jen and C.J., and Jack and David.
episodes.title: Lovelines

episodes.synopsis: As Eddie surprises Joey with an elaborate end-of-the-school-year gift, Pacey's dreams come crashing down on the heels of a favorite stock's meltdown.
episodes.title: Catch-22

episodes.synopsis: As Pacey struggles to tell Dawson about his costly investment debacle, Jen recruits her mother to help Grams face her bout with cancer.
episodes.title: Goodbye, Yellow Brick Road

episodes.synopsis: With the future of Dawson's movie in doubt, Joey rallies their friends to help him realize his dream.
episodes.title: Joey Potter and Capeside Redemption

episodes.synopsis: Five years into the future, Dawson and his friends reunite for his mother's wedding in Capeside.
episodes.title: All Good Things...

episodes.synopsis: As the seriousness of Jen's condition becomes apparent, Dawson and his friends seek to resolve their longstanding differences.
episodes.title: ...Must Come to an End
